   <abstract>This report details the deep economic losses among young families with children and warns of troubling consequences from these losses, for young and old Americans alike. The report reveals that even though America is richer today than ever before, it does not ensure that families have adequate wages and income, education, training, health care, child care, and affordable housing. Many graphs are used to illustrate issues such as poverty rates of children by age and employment of family head, median family income by age of family head and presence of children, change in median income by age of family and presence of children, and homeownership rates of families with children by age of household head.</abstract>
